column5: Finally a fishing day I've been looking for for awhile...enough of that one day good bite next three trips poor....today was the day....great weather...my first day with no wind at all in the morning...and fish cooperated ....  Got lots of whities...the limit and 5 more released....4 hooked but lost...  Got a nice laker 9 Lbs. tried for one more but kept getting whities no matter what dept I tried.... All in all....it was nice trip ...will try few more in the remaining week before season close.  All fish caught on Meegs in the presence of James himself ha ha. Thanks for the company James and his friends. Looking forward to that Algonquin trip in the summer Bud.  Here are few pictures....    And a picture of one of the whities released at the hole.    Cheers,  Ice Fisherman
Nicely done, congrats on a great day.
do they survive after being relesed?
Well done!  got to love that Lake Simcoe Fishery  ID1  BELIEVE
Great stuff Emil.  Wish I was out there today.  Hopefully they'll hang around til the weekend  Joey
Hey!! That's awesome! Nice laker!  Was out at Minet point on Sunday, brutal wind. Was marking a lot of Whitey's on the bottom but got nothing. Glad you had a successful day!
nice fish Like the 'hole shot'  H2whoa! We were at Minets on Sundy as well.  3 people in your group , two in red floater suits ?  TB
